    - *Avoid cognitive work during meals*: Reading, problem-solving, or emotionally demanding conversation should be deferred; eating should be a passive, non-demanding activity
    - *Rest after meals*: Lying supine or semi-recumbent for 30–60 minutes after eating reduces the postural demand on compensatory mechanisms and supports effective digestion
